{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DdAM8Wnxcu3P6sbkWTGDaG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is clear: `PostgresChatMessageHistory` uses sync `SessionLocal()` inside what's called from async `generate_response()`. The fix is to wrap the sync DB operations in `asyncio.to_thread()`.\n\nLet me implement this. The three methods that need fixing:\n1. `messages` property → needs to become an async method\n2. `add_user_message` → async\n3. `add_ai_message` → async\n4. `_add_message` → async\n\nAnd the callers in `generate_response` need to be updated.\n\nAlso `get_agent_for_tenant` in `AIService` is sync and called from `process_incoming_message` which is async.\n\n\nNow I'm wrapping the sync database operations with `asyncio.to_thread()` to handle the blocking calls properly from the async context.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5828,"cache_read_input_tokens":18391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5828},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0b211461-9717-45cb-96b8-b1f56bba86ea","uuid":"3c3235d1-721b-4eb8-b583-5ffebbbf75f8"}
